headline: Winklevosses Lean on MAGA Clout as Gemini’s Losses Mount Ahead of IPO
summary: In a remarkable turnaround, the twins have become central players in the nexus of power between the crypto industry and President Donald Trump’s MAGA complex.  Now the brothers are taking advantage of the moment to raise as much as $433 million for Gemini in an initial public offering expected later this week.  The IPO, though, is laying bare an inconvenient situation: that despite all the trappings of wealth and success, the 44-year-old brothers have faced ongoing difficulty in catching up with rivals and turning their decade-old company into a profitable business.

headline: A Key to Larry Ellison’s Wealth Creation: Years of Oracle Stock Buybacks
summary: Unlike many technology companies,  Oracle  has taken stock buybacks seriously—and that is why its chairman Larry Ellison now rivals Tesla CEO Elon Musk as the world’s wealthiest person, with an Oracle stake worth about $387 billion.  Oracle shares were up 28% to $334 Wednesday in the wake of the company’s earnings report Tuesday.  Oracle’s share count has shrunk by almost 45% over the past 15 years to 2.8 billion shares.

headline: Trade Desk Stock Is Plummeting. Why It Faces Growing Concerns.
summary: Analysts at Morgan Stanley downgraded Trade Desk, citing growing concern about both its connected-TV and internet ad segments, in the latest setback in what is proving to be a nightmare year for the advertising-technology company.  The bank’s Matthew Cost and Brian Nowak moved  Trade Desk  stock to an Equal-weight rating from Overweight and lowered their price target to $50 from $80 in a research note Wednesday.  Trade Desk shares were down 10% to $47.14.
